{
  "stem": "25598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] Before of we crossed the Dniester, because my mother is so clean, she decided to wash me and herself of the mud and of the excrement.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So very early one morning, she took me, when-- when we thought that the gendarmes are still asleep-- she took me to the river.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "By that time-- by that time we knew where the river was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she took me to the river, and on the shores of the river I saw some incredible sights.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were limbs of animals, and limbs of people, and Hebrew prayer books all stained with blood, and torn Torahs, and-- and heads, and arms, and fingers, and breasts, and-- and it was all just lying around.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and we-- we found out later that they slaughtered a lot of the people from [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A lot of the Jewish people were slaughtered there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And we cried, and we washed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And there were bodies floating by on the river.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on the way back, to the-- we stayed-- we-- we did not sleep in the field.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We slept in a-- in a barn, some kind of a barn, which only had a-- it had a roof.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then it had some walls made from logs, but it also had these very big openings for animals to go in.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it had-- it had some straw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'm going back now a little bit, because there was a night that I will never forget.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in-- so in order to stop the wind from blowing, people hung up on the nails-- they hung blankets from our luggage.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and everybody was standing on guard.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the men were on guard.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
